https://leetcode.com/problems/intersection-of-two-linked-lists/?envType=problem-list-v2&envId=linked-list


public class Solution {
    public ListNode getIntersectionNode(ListNode headA, ListNode headB) {
        if (headA == null || headB == null) return null;
        ListNode a=headA;
        ListNode b=headB;
        while(a!=b)
        {
            a = (a == null) ? headB : a.next;
            b = (b == null) ? headA : b.next;
        }
        return a;
    }
}


🔹 Case 1: Lists Intersect
Example:

Code
List A: 1 → 2 → 3
                 ↘
                  7 → 8 → 9
                 ↗
List B:     4 → 5
Two‑Pointer Walkthrough
Start: a=1, b=4

Traverse: a=2, b=5

Traverse: a=3, b=7

Traverse: a=7, b=8

Now both pointers eventually align at node 7.

Condition a == b becomes true → intersection found.

🔹 Case 2: Lists Do Not Intersect
Example:

Code
List A: 2 → 6 → 4
List B: 1 → 5
Two‑Pointer Walkthrough
Start: a=2, b=1

Traverse: a=6, b=5

Traverse: a=4, b=null

Redirect: a=null → headB=1, b=null → headA=2

Continue traversing until both reach null.

Condition a == b only becomes true when both are null.

Return null → no intersection.

🔹 Key Difference
Intersection exists: Pointers meet at a real node reference (same memory address).

No intersection: Pointers only become equal at null after traversing both lists fully.
